n things take a turn th=\r\nat is unforseen, we suffer from agony and grief and then try and shift goal=\r\nposts in a vain attempt at self-justification. This is not a spiritually he=\r\nlpful behavior. Better is to start with the first acknowledgement that we h=\r\nave no clue of God&#39;s Will. It can be anything.\n\n&lt;&lt;.=C2=A0But=C2=A0then can =\r\nwe leave every one =C2=A0on their =C2=A0own karma. Then=C2=A0what=C2=A0is t=\r\nhe way to \n=C2=A0go =C2=A0ahead...to =C2=A0purify =C2=A0ourselves =C2=A0as =\r\n=C2=A0well as =C2=A0those =C2=A0who =C2=A0are =C2=A0suffering?&gt;.\n\nIf you th=\r\nink you can take on others Karma and happily deal with them, please go ahea=\r\nd. I follow a different philosophy. First attain a state of realization whe=\r\nre one is in constant communion with the Divine Will, then act as the Will =\r\ndirects. God, or whatever you chose to name it, is infinitely capable of ru=\r\nnning the universe and managing karma of various entities. Indeed that Infi=\r\nnity is All Powerful, Omnipotent. It has perfectall round knowledge. We don=\r\n&#39;t. Not until a communion is firmly established inside.Till such time whate=\r\nver I do and however pious it may seem to me is still a product of my own c=\r\nonditioned mindand nothing more. That is the naked truth. \n\n\nThere is a dif=\r\nference between compassion and pity. Compassion can arise only when there i=\r\ns detachment inside. For only in seriousdetachment, and a very quite mind i=\r\ns it possible to understand all angles of a problem. A many-sided knowledge=\r\n comes. Then one realizes what exactly needs to be done, if at all anything=\r\n needs be done in a certain situation. Pity on the other hand jumps into ac=\r\ntions, rather is driveninto action without this integral wisdom. It has an =\r\ninternal agitation. When Arjuna refused to kill his Gurus, he was driven ve=\r\nry deeply by a sense of pity. Krshna. OTOH, who works through Immaculate Wi=\r\nsdom knew that only by the deaths of these otherwise great mencan future ge=\r\nnerations be in peace. His vision was far reaching and more consequential. =\r\nThis was Divine Compassion. The actions based on compassion always have a g=\r\nreater impact than pity, for compassion presupposes a settled wide-angle wi=\r\nsdomwhich in turn can arise only in equanimity,\n detachment and internal qu=\r\nietude. The great Gods are always compassionate, but never pitiful. If they=\r\n suffered from pity, then every time someone cries for spiritual realizatio=\r\nn these Great Beings would have rushed down and poured a realized state int=\r\no the consciousness in a single fraction of a second. But they don&#39;t do so.=\r\n Not until they know for sure that the adhara or mind-body is capable enoug=\r\nh to make good use of their energies. They wait for the right time to inter=\r\nvene. That is their unique compassion!\n\nThe thing is, even self purificatio=\r\nn is not done by ourselves. At a point in sadhana one inevitable realizes t=\r\nhat it is a Higher Force that does the purification=C2=A0 process. We are a=\r\nt best, as the Gita describes, are a nimitta-matra. How then can one who ha=\r\ns not reached a stable and Divine Union with the Supreme even think of puri=\r\nfying anyone elsewhen we are not even able to purify ourselves sufficiently=\r\nand are at the mercy of this Infinite and All Capable Force?\n\nA deeper and =\r\ndeeper surrender from all parts of mind and life and body. A sincere, patie=\r\nnt, respectful wait. Positive efforts at self examination and correction. I=\r\nnternal consecration. And waiting for an eventual grace which cannot be con=\r\ntrolled or commanded or demanded. That, IMO, is the way out. Let the busine=\r\nss of running the world be left to God, who is more than capable of doing s=\r\no using a million and one methods.\n\nAs for me, only if I am 101% sanguine t=\r\nhat someone shares an extremely strong karmic bond with me, and my trying t=\r\no help can be useful in some way, ONLY THEN I can make an effort to help, t=\r\nhough it cannot be said if the effort will fructify at all. At one point I =\r\nused to believe, a bit ignorantly, that I could help others. Now all such i=\r\ndeas are being driven out of my head.=C2=A0\n\nThat is how I look at it. I am=\r\n sure others will have their own differing view-points...\n\n\n-Regards\n=C2=A0=\r\nRajarshi\n\n\nawaktam wyaktimApannam manyantE mAmabuddhayah |\nparam bhAwamajAn=\r\nanto mamAwyayamanuttamam ||[7:24]\n\n\n________________________________\n From:=\r\n gaurav tripathi &lt;gaurav_alld@...&gt;\nTo: &quot;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&quot;=\r\n &lt;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&gt; \nSent: Sunday, 3 March 2013 12:21 PM\nSubjec=\r\nt: Re: [vedic-wisdom] Re: Fw: Kundalini syndrome\n \n\n=C2=A0 \nDear Rajarshi N=\r\nandy,\n=C2=A0 =C2=A0I =C2=A0agree =C2=A0with your =C2=A0thoughts =C2=A0that =\r\n=C2=A0there =C2=A0will be inheritance of =C2=A0Karmas =C2=A0of =C2=A0the =\r\n=C2=A0person for =C2=A0whom we =C2=A0are =C2=A0going to =C2=A0do the Homam.=\r\n But if =C2=A0that is what God wanted =C2=A0that we =C2=A0can=C2=A0lessen t=\r\nheir =C2=A0suffering=C2=A0then be it.The cricket field =C2=A0analogy is =C2=\r\n=A0perfect.=C2=A0But=C2=A0then can we leave every one =C2=A0on their =C2=A0=\r\nown karma. Then=C2=A0what=C2=A0is the way to =C2=A0go =C2=A0ahead...to =C2=\r\n=A0purify =C2=A0ourselves =C2=A0as =C2=A0well as =C2=A0those =C2=A0who =C2=\r\n=A0are =C2=A0suffering?\n\n\n\nJust Gaurav\n\n\n\n________________________________\n=\r\n From: rajarshi nandy &lt;rajarshi14@...&gt;\nTo: &quot;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroup=\r\ns.com&quot; &lt;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&gt; \nSent: Saturday, March 2, 2013 11:17 =\r\nAM\nSubject: Re: [vedic-wisdom] Re: Fw: Kundalini syndrome\n \n\n=C2=A0 \nHeaing=\r\n voices in the head or seeing things may or may not be an offshoot of a kun=\r\ndalini awakening. There are plenty of simultaneous things that can happen. =\r\nKundalini is only one phenomenon