ture has a delay mechanism in granti=\r\nng your desires (because of constraints on what Nature can give you right n=\r\now, arising from YOUR\n&gt;  OWN previous actions). So Nature sometimes gives y=\r\nou what you want LATE, when you no longer want it or want something else. F=\r\nor example, one may pray for great wealth one&#39;s whole life and be born as a=\r\n rich but very sick man in next life. One may not enjoy that wealth and pra=\r\ny whole life for health. In the life after that, one may be very healthy, b=\r\nut not have any knowledge or money. In another \n&gt; case, one may deeply desi=\r\nre to act in a famous film. One may be reborn \n&gt; as a tiger or a dog and ac=\r\nt in a famous film, but not really enjoy that \n&gt; experience. Basically, peo=\r\nple keep going in circles through various lives, always &quot;seeking&quot; something=\r\n they are &quot;missing&quot;.\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;Anyway, coming back to Kundalini, if on=\r\ne deeply desires an out of body experience given by a rising Kundalini and =\r\none&#39;s previous karmas constrain one from having it in THIS life, one may be=\r\n born in next life with this specific desire destined to fructify (if there=\r\n is enough karmik force behind it).\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0\n&gt;  *\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=\r\n=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;Kundalini rise is not necessarily scary or painful, if one is we=\r\nll-prepared in terms of attitude and detachment.\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;Once I saw =\r\na chipmunk glued to a mouse trap. I went to free it and it panicked so badl=\r\ny and started to shake violently. I went to save it from a certain slow dea=\r\nth and it was scared that I would kill it!\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;We are like that =\r\nchipmunk, glued to the mouse trap called this body-mind complex and scared =\r\nof being rescued from a certain slow death!\n&gt; &gt